<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM2.2.11">
<l>vāraṇinta koṅkaiyāycci mātavāvuṇ ṇeṉṟamāṟṟam</l>
<l>nīraṇinta kuvaḷaivācam nikaḻanāṟum villiputtūr</l>
<l>pāraṇinta tolpukaḻāṉ paṭṭarpirāṉ pāṭalvallār</l>
<l>cīraṇinta ceṅkaṇmālmēl ceṉṟacintai peṟuvartāmē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master the song of Paṭṭarpirāṉ</l>
<l rend="indent">—he with the ancient fame that decorates the earth—</l>
<l>of Villiputtūr where the perfume of beautiful, dewy water lillies continuously wafts,</l>
<l>with the words, “O Mādhava! Eat!”, of the cowherdess with high, beautiful breasts,</l>
<l>they will obtain a mind that falls upon Red-eyed Māl who is beautiful with excellence.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
